{{notability|Web|date=July 2017}} {{one source|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox website | name = JSFiddle | logo = [[File:Jsfiddle-logo.png|100px|JSFiddle logo]] | founder = Oskar Krawczyk, Piotr Zalewa | slogan = | commercial = No | type = | registration = Optional | language = English | num_users = | launch_date = {{start date and age|2010}} | revenue = | alexa = | ip = | current_status = | footnotes = | programming_language = | homepage = {{URL|https://jsfiddle.net}} }}
'''JSFiddle''' is an [[online community]] for testing and showcasing user-created and collaborational [[HTML]], [[CSS]] and [[JavaScript]] code snippets, known as 'fiddles'. It allows for simulated [[AJAX]] calls.
==History==
JSFiddle started life as an app in 2009 by Piotr Zalewa, originally called MooShell. In 2010, the platform was made freely available when Oskar Krawczyk joined.
In 2017, Michał Laskowski and Andrzej Kała joined the company<ref>[https://jsfiddle.net/about], About JSFiddle</ref>.
